Venter . Derm membranous. With 2 or 3 pairs of long flagellate setae between antennae (each about 18–20 µm long); with rather shorter setae mesad to meso- and metacoxae (11–17 µm long) and even shorter mesad to procoxae; also with a pair of setae medially on abdominal segments II – VII , each about 6–10 µm long. Submarginal setae hairlike, with a seta on each side of abdominal segments I – VII , 2 laterally between spiracles and with 3 on head; also with a submedial line of very short setae (length 2–3 µm) on abdomen (as on
A. gregarius
), with 1 seta on each side of segments I – VII . Microtubular ducts apparently similar to those on dorsum: distribution uncertain but with some submedially on abdomen, in each thoracic segment and near eyespot. Loculate pores with mainly 5 loculi: with 2 or 3 immediately laterad of each peritreme, possibly in small cavity; also with 3 or 4 pores on abdominal segment I between margin and each posterior spiracle.
